reviews.review_text: My go-to pre-concert (or pre-game) spot to grab food that will fill me up, has a gorgeous/ spacious interior and drinks that pack a punch is #AlligatorPear , it's a quick walk to/from Madison Square Garden (also to the LIRR for us commuters).
drinks was yummy but the food lord it's soooooo salty ..., like everything was saltyyyyyyyy . the apps were yummy we got

Social media got me here but the decor and vibes def made an impact. I found this place on a foodie's IG post and I bookmarked it for a while. A Pulsd deal came up and I HAD to grab it. It's an amazing deal - worth every dollar. It comes with a bottle of wine, an app, two entrees, and a dessert. There aren't many waiters/waitresses so it took some time in between each dish but it's fine - we were able to enjoy each other's company and take our sweet time. Very easy and straight forward service and menu and each dish was good. We got the tuna tartare, the blackened salmon, the spicy calabrian pasta, creme brulee cheesecake, and a bottle of cava.

we went with my family and this was our first time trying southern american cuisine and this will definitely not be the last! the nola style louisiana jambalaya is TO DIE FOR! the chicken and andouille gumbo was also good and pretty similar but definitely a bigger fan of the jambalaya :) for an appy the blue crab beignets were perfection

Alligator Pear was a cute venue, where my boyfriend rented out the back room for a patty. It did seem a little empty outside the room when we arrived. Otherwise, the drinks were yummy and the bartenders were sweet.
I love a New Orleans-inspired restaurant!If you do as well, this is a must-visit in Midtown. It's under the same restaurant family as two other great spots: Tara Rose and Bosco.

Took my friend here for a birthday dinner on Tuesday evening, we had an amazing experience!! I don't often feel the strong urge to go back to any restaurant given so many choices in the city but this place I know I'll be back. Our server Cassandra was so kind, and she treated us very well. They gave us free drinks and also comped the beignets we ordered: something I've never experienced before in NYC!
The ambiance of this place is charming and inviting.

Would give somewhere between 3 and 3.5 stars. The dessert was really the star of the show here. Creme brûlée cheesecake was fantastic. Dined here as part of a bachelorette trip. It was not terribly crowded for a Saturday evening. It is a nice looking place. $8 for four tiny rolls I thought was a little steep. Gnocchi was not bad however kind of more like a soup. I think it could've used a little bit more gnocchi as you can see in the pic.
Came here with reservations for dinner with a group of gal pals after a holiday mixer. From the reviews, I could tell the drinks and the ambiance would be immaculate, but the food could be better...
Delicious dinner!! We reserved this restaurant for dinner not knowing it was in the lobby of our hotel so that was a nice surprise!

The Duck Borek and Mezze is crazy good. We did the Chef's menu, which is reasonably priced considering the bananas amount of food provided, there were tons of leftovers good enough to take home. They were also kind enough to do a second dessert to accommodate the vegan at the table, and the charred pineapple stole the show.
Surprise in the middle of Hudson Yards - was delicious. Ambiance, food, and drinks were all 10 out of 10. Shout out to the chef, who I met and was the sweetest.

Let's start with the positives! The interior was beautifully designed and the waiter was nice. However, the most important thing failed to deliver - the food. We started with the dips, which tasted okay but seemed overpriced. Things all went downhill from there. We waited 30 minutes for the mains. When they came out, the Brussels sprouts were burnt to a crisp and inedible. My main dish, the branzino, was also burnt and tasted bland. The fried chicken was okay... but a bucket of KFC would have been better. I usually steer clear from leaving bad reviews but I wanted to leave a warning. I will not be returning.

I recently ended up back at Zou Zou's and had another amazing experience...that even included the same excellent server.  However, instead of sitting in the main dining room, my group was outside on the swanky patio.  I was also pleased to discover that the restaurant had a rooftop area that I will need to explore on my next visit.
A short walk from the Javits Convention my coworkers and I were able to get a quick table, without a reservation, thanks to the host.
The service is great and the ambiance and decor is beautiful! It's part of the Quality restaurants chain and it shows!

Has outdoor and indoor seating and it's lovely to sit outside in the summer. The sangria was delicious and so was the food. We got duck borek, manti and the spreads and kasseri cheese. Manti doesn't taste like a Turkish manti and isn't my favorite here but all the others were amazing. Kasseri cheese was simply amazing and so were the spreads. Service was good - they were decently attentive and brought food quickly. Highly recommend!

I've been here a handful of times and every time is 100/10. Easily my favorite restaurant in the city. Everything I've tried has been absolutely delicious and the service is great. Definitely on the pricier side, we usually spend about $75/person but it gets you a ton of food.
Plenty of food here with a big menu and creative dishes. It is a Mediterranean restaurant with a modern twist. Tables are a bit close and dark ambiance. Service was friendly and average.
This place is awesome. Andrés is the man, he made the experience so fantastic. I would eat here a lot if I were you

Andrés was our server and he took very good care of us. They also have a deal for brunch on the weekend for all you can drink plus 1 appetizer (or dessert) and then 1 entree. The ambiance is very tropical and immersive to the culture of the food. I would highly recommend coming here on a regular basis to try all the different foods.

I love this restaurant. I had previously dined at the Bryant Park location and now I am trying the Chelsea location. It did not disappoint. The ambiance is warm and inviting. The hostess and servers are friendly and helpful. It is the unique and tasty menu that is the winner. It was Sunday brunch so I started with the Guava Screwdriver and the Cuban Sandwich Spring Rolls. Nice.

We came here after a comedy show and lucked up when we found out it was also Latin restaurant week. I've never been to this location but the lobster noodles is just as delicious as the Bryant park location.
We were very excited when we saw Asian/ Cuban fusion as the description.  Us all being Latin and loving Asian food, we thought this place would be perfect.

We went on a Wednesday around 6pm and there were lots of tables available! The interior is very beautiful and the aesthetic was a cool fusion of Cuban x Chinese. Since it was still happy hour, we ordered the lechon on tostones and were not disappointed. The waiter also recommended the Cuban sandwich spring rolls and that was delicious too! Additionally, we got the crispy pig's ears which was my favorite appetizer out of all of them -- crispy and so flavorful. The yucca fries were the biggest disappointment. They were hard and not flavorful, as if they weren't fried long enough or seasoned enough.

Cute decor and spacious. Food is Cuban Asian fusion. We ordered a bunch of entrées to share family style. Service was decent. The food itself was a little over salted and seasoned for our palates and we were very thirsty afterwards. Our favorite was probably the Cuban fried rice, the noodles were also very tasty but too salty.

I don't understand why there's such a high rating of this restaurant. We came during happy hour and had some oysters, they were refreshing and didn't have a gamey flavor. This is a Chinese and Cuban fusion restaurant so I expected dishes to have a mix of flavors but it seemed most of their offerings were either or. We got the fried rice as it was the most fusion option they had but for $28 there was only 3 pieces of shrimp barley any pork and it was mostly rice, plantains, and spam all very cheap ingredients. Nothing was wrong with the taste but I could easily make this dish at home. Service and interior were meh.  I would not return, highly disappointing.

I didn't realize the last time I came to this calle dao was in 2018. I decided to order different items off the menu. Something gave me a bad pain in my stomach. It didn't feel good at all. For the table, we ordered the pork spring rolls,  ropa vieja, flat iron steak, and ma-po maduros. I did like the ropa vieja and flat iron steak.
We visited a few days ago on Sunday evening, a party of 6. Luckily there was no wait and we were seated quickly. The hostess was very kind and asked if we had a preference for high chair placement.
Great food, great service.

I stumbled upon here by accident once when lots of other restaurants were too full to take me and a group. We got here when the restaurant just opened which is lucky because I find out it gets packed QUICK. Food is amazing and the vibes are really nice. I got the kimchi soba my first time here and loved it!
Great food and quick food arrival, but the frustration we had with the wait (1 hour and 40mins) and female host on Friday made me not want to return.
It was so much fun trying so many different things. It was yummy but I feel like I had higher expectations. The drinks were okay. The food came out relatively quick and the vibes were good inside.
Do not hesitate to go here. Bring friends. Eat family style.

I recommend the spicy kimchi udon. It was flavorful, saucy, small pieces of shrimp, cheesey, much like an Italian/japanese/korean fusion dish. I also ordered the okonomiyaki and it was a mistake on my end as I just ate an authentic one in Japan and this didn't compare. So out of the three tapas/entrees I ordered I like this one the least. I can also recommend the yellow tail in ponzu sauce. I was just sad that there's only a few pieces as we inhaled that real quick. It's a great refreshing appetizer and perfect on a hot summers day. Overall a nice vibe here. You can make reservations fyi! I came in as a walk in on Saturday night around prime time and while the front staff said the wait should be 45 min for 2 people we ended up waiting 20 mins.

This restaurant is a hidden gem tucked away in a basement with an ambiance that is dark and cozy. I came here with a total party of 6 on a Tuesday night, and we needed to wait an hour to get seated, but it was worth the wait!

Have you ever been recommended a hip, Korean/Japanese spot in Midtown and been skeptical by the recommender and not by the food? Because this was me, but the food, drinks, and ambiance here at Izakaya MEW are chef's kiss that I want to gate keep so bad but also shout from the rooftops about this restaurant! If you're not able to get a Resy, would recommend stopping by around opening as they are quite accommodating (if your party is small).
First time here & we loved it! Restaurant is on the basement so its easy to miss. Place is spartan looking but clean. Service is fast & efficient.

business_name: Bar Primi Penn District New York 3

reviews.review_text: ### Dinner at Bar Primi
I came for lunch here with colleagues - it was early (before noon!) and we were some of the first ones there but sure enough was filling up by the time we left.

Bar prime was always a go to for me when it came to authentic pasta & frośe so I had to check out the new location. Beautiful location, spacious, indoor/outdoor, patio. BUT I feel like this location is very commercial & touristy. The frośe is on point, thank god that didn't change. There's a lot of new items on the menu, the burrata pockets & Cesar salad was sooo good. The pomodoro was good & classic although I felt the pasta could cook more. We were able to get the frośe tree for dinner even tho it's a brunch item but it was early & the manager was nice enough to give it to us. The tree was $64 which I thought was priced great for 4 drinks. Our waiter was new so she really didn't know much when we asked questions.

The food is average at best - same for service, which was a bit slow and inattentive - but liked the outdoor space a lot. The best dishes were probably the hot knots (love those), chitarra and clams pasta (sauce was good but wish there was more pasta) and the hot girl salami Sicilian square pizza (pretty average). The Caesar salad was okay - didn't love the other pastas, including the fusilli and the pappardelle - which I ordinarily love.

Came here solo on a Saturday afternoon for brunch when I had errands to do in the city. Location is very close to Penn Station which is great! It was pretty empty but I didn't mind that at all. Grabbed a sit at the bar. They do have cute outside seating, where most people were.

reviews.user_location: Corona Del Mar, Newport Beach, CA
reviews.review_text: We were originally supposed to go to Ci Siamo, but we had confusion with our reservation that night. We ended up walking back to my cousins apartment when she said she's been wanting to try Bar Primi. She was talking about how her neighbor has been visiting the restaurant multiple times within the last week, so we walked in and were able to sit right away.

first time trying this new location. The place is beautiful and quite large with a generously sized bar and outdoor space. The only issue with the ambiance is that it is super noisy. Service is attentive and extremely helpful.

The most exciting opening in the 'hood is here! Outside of Blue Ribbon Sushi & Steak,  & the Moynihan food hall & Los Tacos, a new and fabulous Italian restaurant that moved uptown. There's a huge alfresco food terrace we ate at and the food delivered. Ate:
The long anticipated wait is over! Bar Primi is now open in Chelsea...
Delicious! I want to return to try other things on the menu!

Food came out hot and not so tasty, the waiter had below average service. Never have I ever ate at an Italian  restaurant where I had to pour my own water, and the bread was served cold. Slack service gets slack tip. I saw you do it for everyone around me, just not me.
The rum selection alone makes Tavola well worth the visit.
Where do I begin....we have lived in the neighborhood for over 20 years and have been coming here for a long time. Loved this place until we dined here today.
We had reservations and were seated promptly.  They have these long tables where it feels communal style seating.  We didn't mind.
Another great takeout experience from Tavola! Next time, I really need to dine in! It is so cute inside!

Gorgeous intimate dining with delicious food and affordable prices! I'm already planning to come here for my next trip to the city. The gnocchi was delicious and the softest gnocchi I've ever had! The service was attentive and my food came out fairly quick! I saw the braciole on the menu after I ordered and need to come back and try it

We visited Tavola on a Sunday afternoon. We had to call to make a reservation since we had a party bigger than 6 people, but reservations for smaller parties can also be made through Yelp. They also told us we had a 90 minute time limit, but that wasn't really an issue. The restaurant was moderately sized so I understand why they wouldn't want a bigger party staying too long. The interior was very rustic, and I liked the antique glassware the water came in. Our waiter was very attentive and made sure everything was ok throughout the meal.
Took us way too long to check this restaurant out considering it's so close to my boyfriend's condo. So glad we decided on takeout the other night.
Tavola is a reliable brick oven Italian spot that might not be a standout if it were downtown, but up near midtown, is the rate restaurant that takes reservations and isn't a ripoff.
Casual, authentic, affordable. If you are looking for a casual authentic Italian place with good price, you should try this place.
I can't believe I just found this place and already have a ready to go back next week. The food is so well thought out and the staff are A+

When you try to order dips and breads and the waiter tells you one (not two) breads is enough, believe the waiter. My friend and I ordered two dips (the hummus and the spicy whipped feta) and two breads (frena and pita) and we couldn't even order anything else. Which was so tragic because we really wanted the lamb skewer, shish kebab, and crispy squash blossoms. We also got the hot sauce which wasn't spicy at all in our opinion but still tasty.

Now this is a quality restaurant! I came here with my cousin and I was really impressed by the service here. Immediately upon arriving, the hostess was very kind and welcoming.  I got a reservation for 4pm on a Sunday for outside. It happened to be a bit hot out and the table we were going to be seated at was in direct sunlight so we opted to sit inside. Luckily there was enough room inside to it was no issue!
Excellent food (4/5 overall with a few truly standout dishes), but the ambiance/restaurant service really brought down my experience here.
I got a dinner reservation for my birthday and it was the best decision ever -- Shukette has instantly become one of my top favorite restaurants in NYC.
Cute place.

I've passed by Shukette before and it looked like a neighborhood favorite, so I decided to give it a go. I really enjoyed the bold punchiness and the bright magentas and yellows of the Shukette pickles appetizer. Staff seemed constantly on the go. The frena is a must-get. The lamb skewer was fine. The twist soft serve (berry sorbet and tahini) was refreshing though I wish the halva floss was on that one too. The back of the restaurant was also way more hot than the seating towards the front.
Amazing food and amazing vibes!

While food was flavorful, dining experience was not ideal. Please note that this restaurant is family share style so they will bring out all the food in the order in which it is made (not a good place to go if people want their own entrées). The chicken wasn't served until an hour and a half after we were seated at the table so they ended up compensating us for this. With that said, the weight staff is very nice and the Frenna bread in particular is exceptional.
Went with a friend for dinner and was only able to manage a reservation outside, but still decided to try it out.

business_address: 440 West 33rd St Ste 100 New York, NY 10001

reviews.review_text: Food was amazing. I loved the pasta. service was excellent I loved the drinks it was all made from scratch they were very nice and patient
A perfect night. Five stars. Outstanding service,

Went to the restaurant for a private event. The bartender was very friendly and knowledgeable. The food was fresh (scallops, salad) and tasted amazing. We were served both regular and gluten free pasta and I enjoyed both. I tend to avoid desserts, but their cake and parfait were both rich and amazing!  Recommended!
Great experience from start to finish. The ambiance is very chic. Take the elevator up to the second floor, and you will be greeted with wine in the elevator!

The service was exceptional, and the ambiance was beautiful. What truly made me love this restaurant was that the chef prepared an off-menu dish for me because I'm a vegan. It was absolutely delicious, and the non-alcoholic beverage, TONIO, was also refreshing.
Upscale vibes, delightful service and excellent drinks, but don't come here if the only thing you want is good Italian food.
Be sure to walk through the shopping center and office buildings in order to find this restaurant. Otherwise he will be lost.
Came for a friend's birthday on a Friday night and it was PACKED! Kinda hard to find but once you do, take the elevator up a flight. The elevator has mini glasses for you to self pour some wine.

I don't think this place gets enough hype. I've been to some of the top Italian restaurants in the city, and this place blows most of them away. The food and service are unparalleled. After last night's dinner, this is in my top 3 Italian restaurants in NYC.
Delicious dinner!! We came here before a show and my only regret is not coming hungrier since we had a late snack before the early dinner!

address: 440 West 33rd St Ste 100 New York, NY 10001

business_name: Bourbon And Branch New York City
business_address: 155 W 33rd St New York City, NY 10001

reviews.review_text: We had a great breakfast here. Glad we came here early not too many people. It was very relaxing.
So cute! Right by Penn Station and sometimes gets crowded but usually the waitlist goes by quick. Pretty fun to watch a Rangers game here too!
Came here today with a group of friends for lunch.

What a great find near 34th st! We walked in for their happy hour and they were able to accommodate us quickly. We sat at a bar height table near the entrance. We ordered the bacon jam burger and it was incredible - the bacon was so good and the caramelized onions were amazing. I ordered the espresso martini and it was strong and delicious. The margarita tasted like pretty generic margarita mixer so I'd probably skip that next time. Overall, great space for a quick happy hour!

Came here for a snack and happy hour with my bestie. I saw the sliders being ordered at another table and they look delicious... I will be back to try those. Service was whatever, location is great, next to MSG and Penn Station.

It can be difficult to navigate the chain restaurants and bar food that saturate midtown. The area in and around Penn Station is hardly the cultural hub of Manhattan. With the train station and world-famous Madison Square Garden arena being two the of the main drivers of foot traffic, this area is quite....touristy.
This restaurant was recommended by our friend as we visited NY for vacation. The food was amazing and drinks were on point! This place is pretty spacious and love the modern aesthetics!

Let me start by saying that I really enjoyed my experience at this restaurant. The waitress was very attentive and management also checked in to see how our service was going. My sister and I ordered some drinks. I had a glass of Prosecco and she ordered a Sangria. We ordered the dry rub wings with the white sauce and the slider stack. The wings were so good and well prepared. The slider stack came with colossal potato wedges. Everything was so delicious and the atmosphere in the restaurant was very nice. The restaurant is across of Madison Square Garden so it is definitely a great place to pregame before attending a concert or game. My sister and I also placed to go orders and we both ordered the roasted chicken. It was delicious and I enjoyed everything I ate. I'll definitely visit this restaurant again when I'm in Herald Square.

After a thrilling night at Madison Square Garden, finding this gem nearby was a relief. The ambiance was just what we needed - spacious, lively, with the right tunes for both couples and groups. The staff's warmth and efficiency added to the experience. The braised ribs were a delight, tender and flavorful, complemented by the sweet potatoes. Yet, the truffle pasta, while not bad, didn't quite hit the mark. It lacked the finesse in presentation and the richness we anticipated in sauce and cheese. While the truffle essence was there, we couldn't help but feel it fell short of expectations.

We stopped by for a bite to eat, and I haven't been in this establishment since it was Hooters, and my friend was the manager. Great spot, friendly staff, nice and lively atmosphere, and the food and drinks were great. The wings are to die for. I will definitely be back to try other food drink items.

business_address: 23 W 32nd St Fl 3 New York, NY 10001

reviews.review_text: Alex was the sweetest server ever ! The food here is always so good - definitely recommend the spicy bbq vegan meat and also the soybean garden tofu. The space is always comfortable and clean, ~ cute lights and decor and has a street view from the 3rd floor ! Leave a fat tip for my man Alex if you visit !
Really delicious food and chill environment with a fun vibe. Highly recommend this spot to anyone coming new to the city or wanting to try a Korean BBQ spot. The staff is great as well.
Great late-night Korean tapas place! Ordered the popcorn chicken, spicy pork belly bbq and cheesy corn - all tasty
Don't even know where to start

Came here on a Thursday night because they're open late...they didn't disappoint. The summer special is a steal. We had the best pork shoulder, pork belly, and chicken katsu. The chicken was crispyyy. The belly melted in my mouth.
First impressions of the place is that you go to eat and have a good time. The aesthetic of the venue is casual. You can come with a group of friends to enjoy good food and drinks.
Made a reservation for a party of 7+2 kids at 6:30pm
Came here for a late night meal with my friends and found the food to be delicious and filling. We ordered the 2+1 special - order two "main dishes" and you get 1 appetizer for free.

Super overpriced with TINY portions, Korean-American fusion restaurant on the third floor. Would give one more star if the portions were bigger. They were doing a special for May 2024, buy 2 main entrees and get 1 appetizer free. Still not worth...

Came here for a couple drinks and a few appetizers. Upon entering the restaurant, I was told I'd have to make a reservation which is understandable. I made a reservation online for an opening 45 minutes later. I walked around ktown and came back about 15 minutes later because I got bored and was instantly seated with many tables open, which made me think making the reservation was kinda pointless.
